# Opacity & Alpha üëª

## Opacity Property
Sets opacity for the **whole element** (including text).
```css
div {
  opacity: 0.5;
}
```

## RGBA / HSLA
Sets opacity for **only the color** (background or text), leaving children opaque.
```css
div {
  background-color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5);
}
```

# Linear Gradients üèÅ

A linear gradient goes down/up/left/right/diagonally.

Syntax: `background-image: linear-gradient(direction, color1, color2, ...);`

```css
/* Top to Bottom (default) */
background-image: linear-gradient(red, yellow);

/* Left to Right */
background-image: linear-gradient(to right, red, yellow);

/* Diagonal */
background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom right, red, yellow);
```

# Background Shorthand ‚úçÔ∏è

Order matters (mostly).

`color image position/size repeat origin clip attachment`

```css
body {
  background: #ffffff url("img_tree.png") no-repeat right top;
}
```

# Multiple Backgrounds üìö

You can specify multiple background images, separated by commas.

The first image is closest to the user (on top).

```css
body {
  background-image: url(img_flwr.gif), url(paper.gif);
  background-position: right bottom, left top;
  background-repeat: no-repeat, repeat;
}
```

# CSS Variables üß™

Define colors once, use everywhere. Theme changes made easy.

```css
:root {
  --main-bg-color: coral;
  --main-txt-color: white;
}

#div1 {
  background-color: var(--main-bg-color);
  color: var(--main-txt-color);
}
```
